        {
          "reviewTitle": "looks great, but rubs off",
          "reviewText": "This product covers so well and looks perfectly natural. I love the way it makes your skin look perfect. Unfortunately, it does rub off on clothes where the skin rubs on your skin. it will also rub of on sheets if your leg rubs on the edge of sheet when you get into bed. The spots will wash off, you just have to be aware of it. I just love the way it makes my skin look that i keep using it. I do stand in front of a fan for it to dry, but if rubbed with pressure, it will rub off. i do love it.",
          "reviewDate": "Reviewed in the United States on August 9, 2025",
          "customer": "Amazon Customer",
          "customerProfileUrl": "https://www.amazon.com/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AHBCDFH2IGRHB7YROS4KTE65BY4Q",
          "customerStarsRating": 5,
          "productSpecs": {
            "size": "3.3 Fl Oz (Pack of 1)",
            "color": "Medium"
          },
          "helpfulVotes": "5 people found this helpful"
        },
        {
          "reviewTitle": "Please save your money",
          "reviewText": "I am going to be absolutely honest here. I would rather wear foundation from the dollar tree. Yep I'm not kidding I would. At least then I would probably have some coverage. Coverage even with trying to build it up was non-existent. I bought the lightest shade they make and it's still too dark. I'm not that pale of a woman either. I saw reviews that claimed that you can't feel it. You certainly can. It has that sticky kind of feel to it. I don't know about you but I don't want stuff that feels sticky on my face. With this being a Westmore product and them being well known for their makeup work you would think it would be high quality. What a joke. Please don't waste your money on this product. You'll be horribly disappointed like I am if you do",
          "reviewDate": "Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2024",
